Sistema May Acquire Kosmos TV to Get 4G Licenses, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-08-10T06:45:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/sistema-may-acquire-kosmos-tv-to-get-4g-licenses-vedomosti-says.html
AFK Sistema, billionaire  Vladimir
Yevtushenkov ’s holding company, may acquire the Russian state’s
50 percent stake in Kosmos TV to obtain 4G licenses for OAO
Mobile TeleSystems, its wireless unit,  Vedomosti  reported.  Sistema, which already owns 50 percent of the satellite
television operator, may acquire the stake from the state-run
Russian Television & Radio Broadcasting Network, Vedomosti
reported, citing both companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  